eligibilityCriteria.text:
Diagnostic Assessments:
Hematologic abnormalities defined as:

Hemoglobin <9 g/dL (1 transfusion allowed ≤14 days from randomization);

Absolute neutrophils count <1500/mm 3 or <1.5 x 10 9 /L;

Platelets <100,000/mm 3 or <100 x 10 9 /L.

Hepatic dysfunction defined as:

Total bilirubin >1.5 x ULN (≥3 x ULN in case of documented Gilbert's syndrome);

AST and ALT >3 x ULN (>5.0 x ULN in case of liver involvement by the tumor);

ALP >2.5 x ULN (>5 x ULN in case of bone metastasis);

aPTT >1.25 x ULN and INR >1.25 unless the participant is receiving anticoagulation, then aPTT and INR should be within the therapeutic range of the intended use.
